{
  "stem": "7744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And then years later, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] many years later, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was very interesting, because the man who is-- who was director of the North York Board of Education saw me making a presentation to the board.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he said to me, you're Elsa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You sat a couple of rows behind me in school.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, who are you?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, I'm Carl Kinzinger.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I said, Carl, you're the one that was the best student in German and in Latin before I came to York Memorial.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But after I came, you weren't that anymore.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And he had to laugh.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So it was very interesting, that-- that part.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't know why I'm crying, because it's a-- it's a actually a pleasant memory.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the principal of York Memorial at that time, of course, he's many years gone.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He was a man that was very highly respected.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And in fact, when he died, there was a-- [BACKGROUND NOISE] a memorial service and a scholarship in his name.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was called Papa Ainsley.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were not too many people in those days that would have done that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, in-- in-- in-- in school like Harvard Collegiate, where you saw a few more immigrants and all, it was more common.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People were used to seeing Jewish students maybe coming in.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But York Memorial was strictly Anglo-Saxon white.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They-- they didn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't think they knew about the Holocaust.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So that was sort of interesting, and I have very fond memories of the school.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
